icing to examine the phenomenon of the changing nature of policing in Canada. The essays describe the character and constitution of security in Canada and explore the implications of these changes in terms of larger questions about power, social control, justice, and law. Wide-ranging and topical, Re-imagining Policing in Canada will prove essential reading for policy-makers and scholars alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPolicezCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aClarke, Curtis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooley, Dennis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCooly, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEng, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEricson, Richard V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaggerty, Kevin D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHermer, Joe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuey, Laura. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKempa, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMopas, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRigakos, George S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShearing, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStenning, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWood, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package 